## Judge Scoring Eligibility (`validate_judge_scoring_eligibility`)

All must be true (in order):

1. Evaluation criteria exists (`prompt.evaluation_criteria["correctness"]` non-empty list)
2. Pre-review scoring cap: if `initial_review_completed` is False, total scored spans must be `< PRE_REVIEW_SCORED_SPAN_CAP (30)` ‚Äî scoring pauses until the user completes the initial review
3. At least 1 unscored span exists for this prompt
4. No existing PENDING/RUNNING judge scoring job for this prompt

## JSON Parse Failure Retry & Error Storage

When `_evaluate_correctness_with_llm` raises `ValueError` (malformed LLM response):

1. `_evaluate_span_correctness` retries up to `_MAX_EVAL_PARSE_RETRIES = 3` times
2. Each retry makes a fresh `call_llm` invocation (the whole function is re-run)
3. After all retries are exhausted, `_store_span_error(span_id, error_msg)` persists `span.feedback_score["correctness_error"]` and the span is returned as `{"span_id": ..., "error": ..., "eval_error": True}`

### Error span behaviour

- Excluded from all **unscored-span queries**: `_get_unscored_spans`, `_execute_prompt_spans_evaluation`, `validate_judge_scoring_eligibility` ‚Äî all three queries use `and_(~has_key("correctness"), ~has_key("correctness_error"))` as the "not yet evaluated" condition
- Excluded from **scored-span queries** (avg score, prompt tuning, periodic reviews, agent reviews) ‚Äî those all check `has_key("correctness")` which error spans never have
- Excluded from **backtesting source-span selection**: `_fetch_spans_for_backtesting` only fetches spans with `has_key("correctness")` ‚Äî unscored and error spans are never used as backtest inputs. Check 6 in `validate_backtesting_eligibility` applies the same filter.
- When **criteria change**, `correctness_error` is also cleared (alongside `correctness` and `correctness_reason`) so the span gets a fresh evaluation attempt under the new criteria
- `_store_span_score` clears `correctness_error` on successful re-score

### UI error display

- `SpanDetailView` (trace detail panel): shows "Eval error" label instead of score, error message in destructive/80 text
- `SpanFeedbackDialog` (agent review): `ScoreChip` component renders a destructive "Eval error" pill with the message in a tooltip when `correctnessError` is set
- API model `SpanForReview` and TS type both expose `correctness_error`

## When Modifying This Area

- Adding a new evaluation type requires: a new judge prompt pair in `overmind/tasks/utils/prompts.py`, routing logic in `_evaluate_correctness_with_llm`, and possibly a new extractor in `agentic_span_processor.py`
- The `response_type` metadata is set during trace ingestion ‚Äî changes there affect which judge is used
- `ensure_prompt_has_criteria` (from criteria_generator) is called when criteria are missing ‚Äî evaluation won't proceed without criteria for the plain judge. No module-level cache; orchestrators pass a local `criteria_by_prompt` dict for per-batch deduplication.
- All judge prompts must return `{"correctness": float}` JSON ‚Äî the system prompt enforces this. For scores < 0.5, the prompt also instructs the LLM to include `"reason"` (1-2 sentences)
- Scores are stored in `span.feedback_score` JSONB ‚Äî keys: `correctness` (float), `correctness_reason` (str, only when score < 0.5), `correctness_error` (str, only when all parse retries failed), `agent_feedback`, `judge_feedback`
- `correctness` and `correctness_error` are mutually exclusive ‚Äî a span never has both
- When criteria change, `correctness`, `correctness_reason`, and `correctness_error` are all cleared using chained JSONB `-` operators
- The `CorrectnessResult` Pydantic model has `correctness: float` and `reason: str | None` ‚Äî reason is extracted from the parsed JSON only when score is below threshold
- `_store_span_score(span_id, correctness, reason=None)` ‚Äî removes stale `correctness_reason` and `correctness_error` when re-scoring a span
- `_store_span_error(span_id, error)` ‚Äî removes `correctness` and `correctness_reason`, sets `correctness_error`
